iled.\r\n\r\n\r\n=jave\xc2\xb4 lin= (jav): a short spear used for throwing.\r\n\r\n=joc\xc2\xb4 u lar\xc2\xb4 i ty=: mirth.\r\n\r\n=joc\xc2\xb4 und=: merry; sportive.\r\n\r\n=Jove=: the king of the gods; here, the chief person of the household.\r\n\r\n=jun\xc2\xb4 to=: a group of men; a council.\r\n\r\n\r\n=ka lei\xc2\xb4 do scope=: an instrument in which small pieces of colored glass\r\nslide about and form pleasing shapes.\r\n\r\n=Ki was\xc2\xb4 sa=: a name for the Great Spirit, or God.\r\n\r\n=Knights Templar=: an order of knights serving in Palestine and taking\r\ntheir name from a palace in Jerusalem called Solomon\'s Temple.\r\n\r\n\r\n=la goons=: lakes connecting with the sea.\r\n\r\n=La Mort= (mor): "Death," sounded on a horn when the game is killed.\r\n\r\n=la\xc2\xb4 tent=: hidden; not revealed; also, in preparation.\r\n\r\n=leg-bail=: escape by flight.\r\n\r\n=Ley\xc2\xb4 den jar=: a glass bottle used to accumulate electricity.\r\n\r\n=log\xc2\xb4 a rith\xc2\xb4 mic tables=: mathematical tables used to calculate a ship\'s\r\nposition.\r\n\r\n=Long House=: a name for the Iroquois Indians, derived from their long\r\ncommunal houses.\r\n\r\n=lon\xc2\xb4 gi tude=: distance on the earth\'s surface from east to west.\r\n\r\n=lu\xc2\xb4 mi na ry=: a body that gives light.\r\n\r\n\r\n=Ma belle mere= (mare): "My pretty mother."\r\n\r\n=Ma\xc2\xb4 gi ans=: wise men of ancient Persia.\r\n\r\n=mal\xc2\xb4 a dy=: disease.\r\n\r\n=Mal voi sin= (mal vwa zan\xc2\xb4): a Norman baron.\r\n\r\n=man\xc2\xb4 i cure set=: instruments used on the finger nails.\r\n\r\n=man\xc2\xb4 tel et=: a movable shelter of wood.\r\n\r\n=ma rau\xc2\xb4 ders=: robbers.\r\n\r\n=mar\xc2\xb4 i=: husband.\r\n\r\n=masque= (mask): a kind of theatrical performance.\r\n\r\n=mas\xc2\xb4 que rad\xc2\xb4 ing=: going in disguise.\r\n\r\n=ma ter\xc2\xb4 nal=: motherly.\r\n\r\n=mat\xc2\xb4 ins=: a morning service of the ancient church.\r\n\r\n=mer\xc2\xb4 ce na ry=: a hired soldier; a hireling.\r\n\r\n=mer\