=: the place of devils; also, and usually, a riotous\r\nscene.\r\n\r\n=pan\xc2\xb4 nier= (yer): a wicker basket.\r\n\r\n=par\xc2\xb4 ley=: talk; discussion.\r\n\r\n=Pas\xc2\xb4 pa heghs= (hays): an Indian tribe of Virginia.\r\n\r\n=patched=: adorned with small patches of black cloth.\r\n\r\n=pa\xc2\xb4 thos=: sadness.\r\n\r\n=pa visse\xc2\xb4=: a large shield.\r\n\r\n=Pax\xc2\xb4 vo bis\xc2\xb4 cum=: "Peace be with you!"\r\n\r\n=pem\xc2\xb4 mi can=: powdered meat pressed into cakes.\r\n\r\n=per\xc2\xb4 i scope=: an instrument projecting above a submarine which gives a\r\nview of the sea surface.\r\n\r\n=per\xc2\xb4 pen dic\xc2\xb4 u lar=: straight up and down.\r\n\r\n=per\xc2\xb4 pen dic\xc2\xb4 u lar\xc2\xb4 i ty=: straightness up and down.\r\n\r\n=pet\xc2\xb4 ri fied=: turned to stone.\r\n\r\n=phil\xc2\xb4 o soph\xc2\xb4 i cal=: wise; learned.\r\n\r\n=pil\xc2\xb4 lion= (yun): a cushion used by women in riding horseback.\r\n\r\n=pi lote= (pe loat\xc2\xb4): an aeroplane pilot.\r\n\r\n=pin\xc2\xb4 na cle=: summit.\r\n\r\n=pipe=: a musical instrument resembling a flute.\r\n\r\n=plain\xc2\xb4 tive ly=: complainingly.\r\n\r\n=plan\xc2\xb4 i sphere=: the representation of the earth on a plane; a map of the\r\nworld.\r\n\r\n=Ple ia des= (ple\xc2\xb4 ya dees): a group of six stars in the constellation\r\nTaurus.\r\n\r\n=pol lute\xc2\xb4=: to stain; to befoul.\r\n\r\n=po made\xc2\xb4=: a perfumed ointment.\r\n\r\n=po ma\xc2\xb4 tum=: a perfumed ointment.\r\n\r\n=pon\xc2\xb4 der a ble=: weighable; having heaviness.\r\n\r\n=pon\xc2\xb4 der ous=: heavy; unwieldy.\r\n\r\n=pon\xc2\xb4 iard= (yard): a dagger.\r\n\r\n=por\xc2\xb4 tents=: signs; omens.\r\n\r\n=Pow\xc2\xb4 ha tan=: the James river; also the name of Opechancanough\'s\r\npredecessor.\r\n\r\n=pre ca\xc2\xb4 ri ous=: uncertain; dangerous.\r\n\r\n=pre\xc2\xb4 con cep\xc2\xb4 tion=: a foreshadowing; an idea of something to come.\r\n\r\n=pri me\xc2\xb4 val=: original.\r\n\r\n=prim\xc2\xb4 i tive=: original; coming down from afar.\r\n\r\n=Pro\xc2\xb4 cy on= (si): a first-magnitude star.\r\n\r\n=pro di gious= (pro dij\xc2\xb4 us): immense.\r\n\r\n=pro ject\xc2\xb4 ile=: something projected with force, or fired.\r\n\r\n=pur veyed\xc2\xb4=: brought.\r\n\r\n\r\n=quarter-staff=: a short pole, used as a walking-staff and a weapon.\r\n\r\n\r\n=ra\xc2\xb4 di us=: the distance from the center of a body to its surface.\r\n\r\n=rail\xc2\xb4 ler y=: jesting.\r\n\r\n=ran\xc2\xb4 som=: a sum paid for the release of a prisoner.\r\n\r\n=rar\xc2\xb4 e fac\xc2\xb4 tion=: the making thin; less dense.\r\n\r\n=ra\xc2\xb4 ti o=: rate; measure.\r\n\r\n=re cip\xc2\xb4 ro ca ted=: returned.\r\n\r\n=re cum\xc2\xb4 bent=: lying down.\r\n\r\n=re fec\xc2\xb4 to ry=: a dining-room in a convent.\r\n\r\n=re frac\xc2\xb4 tion=: the bending from a straight line which occurs when a ray\r\nof light passes out of the air into water.\r\n\r\n=reg\xc2\xb4 u la tor=: a contrivance for controlling motion.\r\n\r\n=re mu\xc2\xb4 ner a ted=: rewarded; presented with.\r\n\r\n=re nowned\xc2\xb4=: famous.\r\n\r\n=re plete\xc2\xb4=: filled.\r\n\r\n=rep\xc2\xb4 ro ba\xc2\xb4 tion=: condemnation; disapproval.\r\n\r\n=res\xc2\xb4 pi ra\xc2\xb4 tor=: a device covering the mouth and nose and preventing the\r\nbreathing of outside air.\r\n\r\n=ret\xc2\xb4 i nue=: a train of attendants.\r\n\r\n=re ver\xc2\xb4 ber a ted=: reflected; echoed.\r\n\r\n=rime=: hoarfrost.\r\n\r\n=Rolfe, John=: the first Englishman to plant tobacco in Virginia; the\r\nhusband of Pocahontas.\r\n\r\n=rood=: cross.\r\n\r\n=ro\xc2\xb4 sa ry=: a string of beads used in counting prayers.\r\n\r\n=ru\xc2\xb4 bi cund=: ruddy; red.\r\n\r\n=rucksack=: a napsack worn by Arctic travelers.\r\n\r\n=rue\xc2\xb4 ful=: sad; distressed.\r\n\r\n=ruffle=: a contest.\r\n\r\n\r\n=sar cas\xc2\xb4 ti cal ly=: ironically; humorously.\r\n\r\n=sat\xc2\xb4 el lite=: an attendant; also, a body revolving around another, as\r\nthe moon.\r\n\r\n=scar=: a cliff.\r\n\r\n=sci\xc2\xb4 en tist=: one learned in the natural sciences, as chemistry,\r\nphysics, etc.\r\n\r\n=screen=: a surface on which the reflection from the periscope is thrown.\r\n\r\n=sem\xc2\xb4 blance=: likeness.\r\n\r\n=serf=: a kind of slave; an unfree laborer.\r\n\r\n=sex\xc2\xb4 tant=: an instrument used to determine a ship\'s position by\r\nobserving the sun and other objects.\r\n\r\n=Shah=: ruler; king.\r\n\r\n=shrift=: confession made to a priest.\r\n\r\n=Shrovetide=: the days just before the beginning of Lent.\r\n\r\n=sib\xc2\xb4 yl=: prophetess.\r\n\r\n=side drift=: the drift of a vessel to one side or the other of a course.\r\n\r\n=sil hou ette= (sil oo et\xc2\xb4): the black shadow of an object.\r\n\r\n=sin\xc2\xb4 gu lar\xc2\xb4 i ty=: strangeness.\r\n\r\n=smock race=: a race in which the contestants are hampered by garments.\r\n\r\n=sliv\xc2\xb4 er=: a long splinter.\r\n\r\n=sol\xc2\xb4 ace=: comfort.\r\n\r\n=so phis\xc2\xb4 ti ca ted=: experienced; worldly-wise.\r\n\r\n=spec\xc2\xb4 tral=: of graded colors.\r\n\r\n=spin\xc2\xb4 et=: a musical instrument like a piano.\r\n\r\n=spoor=: trail; foot-marks.\r\n\r\n=sprint\xc2\xb4 er=: a runner; a foot-racer.\r\n\r\n=spume=: froth; foam.\r\n\r\n=stac ca\xc2\xb4 to=: disconnected; jerky.\r\n\r\n=states\xc2\xb4 man=: one concerned in the governing of a country.\r\n\r\n=sten to\xc2\xb4 ri an=: loud; thundering.\r\n\r\n=stodg\xc2\xb4 i ly=: with distended eyes.\r\n\r\n=sto\xc2\xb4 ic al ly=: patiently; without complaint.\r\n\r\n=stoke-hold=: the room containing a ship\'s boilers.\r\n\r\n=stra\xc2\xb4 ta=: the layers of rock composing the crust of the earth.\r\n\r\n=strat\xc2\xb4 e gy=: the use of artifice; clever planning.\r\n\r\n=Stuy\xc2\xb4 ves ant=: a Dutch colonial governor of New York.\r\n\r\n=sub lim\xc2\xb4 i ty=: grandeur; magnificence.\r\n\r\n=sub\xc2\xb4 ter ra\xc2\xb4 ne an=: beneath the earth; in a cavity.\r\n\r\n=sump\xc2\xb4 ter mule=: a beast of burden.\r\n\r\n=sump\xc2\xb4 tu a ry=: relating to expense.\r\n\r\n=sump\xc2\xb4 tu ous=: plentiful; extravagant.\r\n\r\n=su\xc2\xb4 per flu\xc2\xb4 i ty=: more than is needed.\r\n\r\n=su per\xc2\xb4 flu ous=: not needed.\r\n\r\n=sur\xc2\xb4 plice=: a white outer garment worn by priests.\r\n\r\n=Sus\xc2\xb4 que han\xc2\xb4 nocks=: an Indian tribe originally inhabiting Maryland and\r\nPennsylvania.\r\n\r\n=sword of Damascus=: a sword made from steel wrought in Damascus, Syria.\r\n\r\n=syl\xc2\xb4 van=: of the woods.\r\n\r\n=sym\xc2\xb4 pho ny=: harmony; music.\r\n\r\n\r\n=ta\xc2\xb4 bor=: a small drum.\r\n\r\n=tac\xc2\xb4 i turn= (tas): silent.\r\n\r\n=tam\xc2\xb4 bour frame=: frame for embroidery.\r\n\r\n=tap\xc2\xb4 es try=: a curtain for a wall ornamented with worked pictures.\r\n\r\n=tar\xc2\xb4 get=: a small shield.\r\n\r\n=ter\xc2\xb4 ma gant=: quarrelsome; scolding.\r\n\r\n=ter\xc2\xb4 ra fir\xc2\xb4 ma=: the firm earth.\r\n\r\n=thane=: a Saxon land-owner.\r\n\r\n=thatch=: straw or reeds.\r\n\r\n=Ti\xc2\xb4 tan=: a giant of Greek myth.\r\n\r\n=tithe=: a tenth.\r\n\r\n=tor\xc2\xb4 toise-shell=: the shell of a turtle.\r\n\r\n=traction engine=: a locomotive that draws vehicles along roads.\r\n\r\n=treasurer=: George Sandys.\r\n\r\n=tri bu\xc2\xb4 nal=: a court of justice.\r\n\r\n=trump=: the card that takes other cards in a game.\r\n\r\n=truss=: tie.\r\n\r\n=tu mul\xc2\xb4 tu ous=: riotous; very noisy.\r\n\r\n\r\n=ul\xc2\xb4 tra ma rine\xc2\xb4=: deep blue.\r\n\r\n=uncle=: a familiar form of address used by jesters.\r\n\r\n=u nique\xc2\xb4= (neek): singular; unusual.\r\n\r\n=u\xc2\xb4 su ry=: unlawful, or excessive interest.\r\n\r\n\r\n=vas\xc2\xb4 sals=: subjects; dependents.\r\n\r\n=ve\xc2\xb4 he ment=: passionate; forceful.\r\n\r\n=ve loc\xc2\xb4 i ty=: speed.\r\n\r\n=vel\xc2\xb4 lum=: leather.\r\n\r\n=ven\xc2\xb4 er a\xc2\xb4 tion=: respect; reverence.\r\n\r\n=ver\xc2\xb4 dure=: vegetation; green growth.\r\n\r\n=ver\xc2\xb4 i ta ble=: true; unmistakable.\r\n\r\n=vic\xc2\xb4 ar=: a clergyman in charge of a parish.\r\n\r\n=vis\xc2\xb4 count=